It was some time after Yuia-sama and I arrived in this
town...

Keeping the memories of my father and mother... and the
bloodstained homeland we were chased from close to my heart,
it was when we finally started to walk on our own two feet.

Overcoming despair... and beginning to believe that it would
eventually turn into hope, it was around the time we started
to feel relieved that it was coming true...

The name of the person who sent the letter was... Seno. My
mother.

That day we were chased from our homeland, amidst the
sorrow, I parted from my father and mother. It was a letter
addressed to me from my mother.

I didn't understand what it meant at all. However, I thought
I should inform Yuia-sama about the details.

But... at this time, Yuia-sama was out in the suburbs for
on-site instruction with the vigilante group.
I waited for the night with an uneasy feeling...

And then... as time passed and I resolved to forget
everything, I realized that my body was no longer solely my
own.

Still... in pursuit of peace, I was living with my feet
firmly on the ground, looking forward, when suddenly...
I heard something unexpected from Lord Yuia.

\N<Hojiko>Hey, isn't that Segi-chan? Are you coming back from the
hospital?
\N<Segi>Yes. Hello, Hojiko-san.

\N<Hojiko>How's your progress? I'm oddly concerned even though it's
not about me.
\N<Segi>Yes... thanks to you.

\N<Hojiko>With that body of yours, you mustn't overdo it, okay? If
something happened to you, Yuia-san would be sad too. If
there's anything I can do to help, don't hesitate to ask,
alright?
\N<Segi>Thank you for your concern.
\N<Hojiko>Yeah, yeah, but still, to think that Segi-chan...
\N<Hojiko>So, um, is it okay if I touch your belly...?
\N<Segi>Eh...? Oh, um...

\N<Hojiko>Heh, hehe... just kidding. I hope it's a healthy child. If
it's a girl, she'll grow up to be as cute as her mom, right?
That's exciting.
\N<Segi>Ha... yes.

\N<Man>Ever since those Luda guys started stationing in this town,
the future's been uncertain, but you can rest easy. After
all, Yuia is someone you can rely on.

It's been several days since Lord Yuia left the city... A
message has reached me.

It detailed how he successfully infiltrated Luda's garrison
and that he's getting closer to finding clues about my
mother and the Princess Consort, but hasn't reached a
conclusion yet.

And then... it said he would spend a few more days at
Luda's garrison to gather information.

Of course, I'm concerned about the safety of my mother and
the Princess Consort, but even more so, I'm worried about
Lord Yuia's safety.

Fortunately, it seems he hasn't fallen into any situation
where his identity would be exposed, and I breathed a sigh
of relief.

Yes... in just ten more days, I'll be able to see Lord Yuia
again.
It was then... that I met that man.

\N<Luda Soldier>...We've finally arrived, Captain Tseda.

\N<Tseda>Hmph, so this is the town with that so-called ruins. Quite a
modest place, isn't it?
\N<Rozaro>...I've been waiting for you, Tseda.
\N<Tseda>Oh? Isn't that Rozaro? What brings you to a place like this?

\N<Rozaro>I took a shortcut instructed by the squad and arrived here
before you. Do you need an explanation?

\N<Tseda>Nah, I guess it's pretty much what I thought, right? You've
come chasing after us on the squad's orders?

\N<Rozaro>If you understand that much, then this will be quick. Return
to the squad with me.
\N<Tseda>Heh, you think I'd just obediently listen to that?
\N<Rozaro>...No.

\N<Tseda>Right? After all, if I return to the squad, wouldn't I just
be bound and hanged on suspicion of rebellion?

\N<Tseda>Ah-ah, what a shame. Even this time, I acted thinking about
Luda's future in my own way.
\N<Rozaro>...You went too far. Accept this as fate and give up.

\N<Tseda>Heh, which one of us is it? Who do you think has the
advantage in this situation?
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Tseda>You see, I'm going to get it. Something in this town that
Luda wants. Then I'll negotiate. Always on equal terms with
Luda.

\N<Yuia>Segi!!
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...
\N<Yuia>I was worried... Where have you been until this late...?
\N<Segi>...I went shopping... and I lost something very important.

\N<Segi>I was... looking for it. But... but I couldn't find it in
the end...
\N<Yuia>...Segi...?

\N<Segi>The thing I lost... will never... return to my hands again.
But... that's okay...
\N<Segi>I can... give up on it properly...

\N<Yuia>...I see. Was it something you received from Seno or Orugi?
If so, it must be very important, and I was insensitive.
\N<Segi>It's not like that...

\N<Yuia>But... to me, there is nothing more important now than you.
I want you to understand that. That's why... I'm glad you're
safe.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...

The face... that smile. That's what I wanted to protect. For
this person... to continue seeing the face of the one I
love.

If that's the case... then even what happened to me was
necessary, and I can accept it.
But why... I wonder?

Why couldn't I... see the face of the one I love at that
moment...?
